16:11.300 --> 16:12.400
There's no money, Alan.

16:13.100 --> 16:14.000
None?

16:14.400 --> 16:16.300
The whole thing's
a house of cards.

16:18.500 --> 16:19.300
Huh.

16:25.400 --> 16:27.200
Okay, I did not want
to have to do this.

16:28.100 --> 16:29.800
But I am Matthew Broderick.

16:31.000 --> 16:32.900
And that is my brother
lying there.

16:33.100 --> 16:35.400
MAN:
I'm so sorry,
Mr. Broderick.

16:35.400 --> 16:37.000
<i>I loved you
in The oducers.</i>

16:37.000 --> 16:37.800
Thank you.

16:39.200 --> 16:41.400
Okay, let's have
a look-see, huh?

16:43.800 --> 16:46.800
According to your tests,
you just had an acute
attack of indigestion.

16:49.900 --> 16:50.900
It was gas?

16:50.900 --> 16:53.100
Yes, a big bubble,
about the size
of a pomegranate.

16:54.400 --> 16:56.200
What have you had
to eat recently?

16:56.400 --> 16:57.800
Nothing much.

16:57.800 --> 17:00.800
He had Belgian waffles,
link sausages, two Red Bulls,

17:00.800 --> 17:01.900
a quart of scotch

17:01.900 --> 17:03.900
and the tongue of
a 24-year-old actress.

17:04.200 --> 17:05.800
He asked what I ate, Alan.

17:06.099 --> 17:07.700
And I told him, Charlie.

17:08.800 --> 17:11.400
Oh-ho, you're
a dirty bird.

17:13.000 --> 17:16.800
Well, the good news is that you
are a perfectly healthy
50-year-old man.

17:17.500 --> 17:18.800
I'm only 40.

17:19.000 --> 17:20.099
Tell that to
your liver.

17:22.400 --> 17:25.700
I recommend you slow down a bit.
I've been saying the same thing.

17:25.700 --> 17:26.599
And you...

17:27.300 --> 17:29.600
<i>Why no sequel to
Ferris Bueller, huh?</i>

17:30.300 --> 17:31.700
I wait and I wait.

17:32.300 --> 17:34.300
I'm sorry;
I'll get on it.

17:34.300 --> 17:36.100
Ah. Give the people
what they want.

17:42.100 --> 17:44.200
So, gas.

17:46.200 --> 17:47.000
Good news, huh?

17:47.700 --> 17:49.700
A little embarrassing, but yeah.

17:50.200 --> 17:51.600
What do you have
to be embarrassed about?

17:51.800 --> 17:55.100
Oh, I don't know-- the
paramedics, thambulance,

17:55.100 --> 17:57.700
the crying and the last-minute
negotiations with God.

17:58.900 --> 17:59.700
Oh, right.

17:59.700 --> 18:02.200
Are you still planning
on teaching piano to orphans?

18:02.400 --> 18:03.600
If any show up, sure.

18:05.600 --> 18:07.200
Well, will you at least
accept the fact

18:07.200 --> 18:08.600
that you have to slow down?

18:10.300 --> 18:11.800
Yeah, yeah.

18:13.400 --> 18:14.800
It's weird, Alan.

18:16.300 --> 18:20.300
It seems like just yesterday I
could... I could party all night

18:20.800 --> 18:22.600
and eat and drink
anything I wanted to.

18:23.000 --> 18:25.100
Now a couple of Red Bulls
and a waffle,

18:25.100 --> 18:27.700
and I'm sitting in the emergency
room praying for a fart.

18:32.800 --> 18:35.700
Now you know why I ordered
tomato juice and cottage cheese.

18:37.200 --> 18:39.200
I got to admit, yodo
take good care of yourself.

18:39.200 --> 18:40.000
I try.

18:41.100 --> 18:42.700
I guess that's why
I keep you around.

18:43.000 --> 18:44.300
Because I'm a good example?

18:44.500 --> 18:46.600
No, you clod,
spare parts.

18:51.900 --> 18:53.000
What are we watching?

18:53.800 --> 18:55.200
<i>Antiques Roadshow.</i>

18:56.800 --> 18:59.400
This woman thinks she has
Martha Washington's
butter churn.

19:02.700 --> 19:03.800
Toaster pizza?

19:04.500 --> 19:05.300
Thank you.

19:06.500 --> 19:07.500
So, you going
out tonight?

19:07.500 --> 19:09.100
Eh, what's the point?

19:10.800 --> 19:13.400
Look, Charlie, I'm glad
you're slowing down a bit,

19:13.400 --> 19:15.500
but you haven't been out
of the house in a week.

19:16.200 --> 19:17.600
Eh, it's too depressing.

19:18.300 --> 19:20.400
Wherever I go,
I'm the oldest guy in the room.

19:21.900 --> 19:22.700
Even here.

19:27.900 --> 19:29.600
Hey, what would you think
about getting a cat?

19:32.300 --> 19:33.100
Okay, that's it.

19:33.100 --> 19:35.000
Put some clothes on.
We're going out.

19:35.400 --> 19:36.800
It's 9:00.

19:36.800 --> 19:38.300
I was going to make
some kettle corn.

19:38.300 --> 19:40.600
Forget the corn;
you're coming with me.

19:41.000 --> 19:42.000
Where are we going?

19:42.000 --> 19:42.800
You'll see.

19:44.400 --> 19:45.900
Can you drive?

19:46.600 --> 19:48.200
I don't like to drive
at night.

19:51.900 --> 19:53.100
What the hell is
this place?

19:53.100 --> 19:54.500
The fountain of youth.

19:54.700 --> 19:55.500
What?

19:55.500 --> 19:56.300
Follow me.

20:01.500 --> 20:04.600
Ooh, look, young stuff.

20:07.000 --> 20:09.300
??????????

20:14.800 --> 20:16.700
May I ask you
a personal question?

20:17.500 --> 20:18.300
Sure.

20:18.500 --> 20:19.700
How old are you?

20:20.000 --> 20:21.200
I just turned 40.

20:21.200 --> 20:23.700
Oh, you're a baby.

20:25.000 --> 20:27.400
well
Yeah.

